WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.370 --> 00:00:05.370
- I see threads, pages,
Instagram accounts,

00:00:05.460 --> 00:00:07.600
that are all about fitness motivation,

00:00:07.600 --> 00:00:09.720
or weight loss motivation.

00:00:09.720 --> 00:00:14.430
Well, there's a problem
with seeking motivation

00:00:14.430 --> 00:00:17.310
in that it usually
revolves around pictures

00:00:17.310 --> 00:00:22.020
or videos of individuals who may be

00:00:22.020 --> 00:00:25.750
10,000 decisions away from being

00:00:25.750 --> 00:00:28.910
at a fitness level of where you are.

00:00:28.910 --> 00:00:33.900
So, for example, pictures
of Arnold Schwarzenegger,

00:00:33.900 --> 00:00:37.640
or Jeremy Buendia, these
are people who are at

00:00:37.640 --> 00:00:40.340
the absolute peak of physical development.

00:00:40.340 --> 00:00:44.240
Even NFL players, absolute
peak, perfect genetics,

00:00:44.240 --> 00:00:45.820
all sorts of things.

00:00:45.820 --> 00:00:49.840
And so when somebody
presents you with a potential

00:00:49.840 --> 00:00:51.900
bad decision, like they
put a chocolate cake

00:00:51.900 --> 00:00:55.363
in front of you, you think,
oh, I have 10,000 steps to go,

00:00:56.580 --> 00:00:59.760
so if I just screw this one
step up, it's not gonna make

00:00:59.760 --> 00:01:01.340
that much of a difference.

00:01:01.340 --> 00:01:02.823
That is fake news.

00:01:03.740 --> 00:01:08.740
So, it's much easier instead of looking

00:01:08.780 --> 00:01:12.350
for motivation, what
you need is discipline.

00:01:12.350 --> 00:01:15.563
Because discipline you can use,

00:01:16.520 --> 00:01:18.030
very simple decision making process.

00:01:18.030 --> 00:01:20.570
This is a lizard brain process.

00:01:20.570 --> 00:01:22.550
Do you wanna wake up tomorrow morning

00:01:22.550 --> 00:01:24.800
and be the guy who
screwed up your principles

00:01:24.800 --> 00:01:27.340
and decided to break
from what you've already

00:01:27.340 --> 00:01:28.970
committed yourself to?

00:01:28.970 --> 00:01:30.560
Or not?

00:01:30.560 --> 00:01:33.020
So it's one decision, it's one decision,

00:01:33.020 --> 00:01:35.210
one moment, one day.

00:01:35.210 --> 00:01:37.730
So I asked a friend of
mine who's really been

00:01:37.730 --> 00:01:39.757
struggling to lose weight, he says,

00:01:39.757 --> 00:01:41.087
"well, I don't wanna give up pizza,

00:01:41.087 --> 00:01:42.060
"I don't wanna give up beer,

00:01:42.060 --> 00:01:43.290
I don't wanna give up chocolate cake."

00:01:43.290 --> 00:01:44.990
It turns out he doesn't
really wanna give up anything,

00:01:44.990 --> 00:01:47.090
and I said, "look, have you ever had a day

00:01:48.401 --> 00:01:52.020
without pizza, or without
beer, or without soda?"

00:01:52.020 --> 00:01:53.570
Ya, of course, right.

00:01:53.570 --> 00:01:55.950
You're traveling,
whatever, didn't get that,

00:01:55.950 --> 00:01:57.830
and you had something else.

00:01:57.830 --> 00:02:00.300
So if you made it through one day

00:02:00.300 --> 00:02:03.670
and you didn't go insane,
then maybe you can make it

00:02:03.670 --> 00:02:05.183
through another day.

00:02:05.183 --> 00:02:08.490
And then if you make these
decisions day by day,

00:02:08.490 --> 00:02:13.490
nutrition is much easier, and
you don't have those moments.

00:02:13.760 --> 00:02:16.030
So when you sit down,
and you have a choice

00:02:16.030 --> 00:02:19.200
between ordering that really healthy meal

00:02:19.200 --> 00:02:21.890
or having nachos with your friends, say,

00:02:21.890 --> 00:02:24.880
yeah, I don't wanna be that person today.

00:02:24.880 --> 00:02:26.800
I wanna be the person that stuck

00:02:26.800 --> 00:02:28.900
to what I committed myself to.

00:02:28.900 --> 00:02:31.670
And it's much easier to stay on that path,

00:02:31.670 --> 00:02:33.850
and then day, after day, after day,

00:02:33.850 --> 00:02:38.850
10,000 decisions later, or
less, you have what you want.

